answerText: Cope Rearrangement [also accept Oxy-Cope Rearrangment; prompt on Cope Reaction; do not accept Cope Elimination][10] Similar to the Cope Rearrangement, this rearrangement sees an allyl vinyl ether converted thermally to an unsaturated carbonyl compound. This reaction's namesake also names a condensation occuring between two esters.

question: Question: For 10 points each, name some chemical reactions that all have something in common: [10] This reaction is the thermal isomerization of a 1,5-diene to a more stable 1,5-diene regioisomer. It may help you to know that the Oxy form of this reaction features a hydroxyl group on the pre-isomerized 1,5-diene.
